description: Rails 8 Service Object Rules
globs:
  - "app/services/**/*.rb"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Service Objects

- Location: app/services/
- Naming: descriptive with verb (AnalystService, ScenarioCalculatorService)
- Always use a call class method as entry point
- Always return a result object or raise a specific error
- Never call external APIs directly from controllers or models
- Claude: use `Ai.ask`, `Ai.chat`, or `Ai.json` only (`rails_ai.mdc`) — never `Anthropic::Client` or `AiRouter`
- Structured Claude output: `Ai.json(system:, keys:, messages:|prompt:, defaults: {})` — do not hand-parse JSON in services
- ENV: use `AppConfig` (`rails_helpers.mdc`) — never `ENV.fetch` in services
- Season year: use `CurrentSeason.year` / `benchmark_year` — not `Date.current.year`
- Controllers rescue AI errors via `include RescuesAi` — not inline rescue blocks
- Long-running Claude work: enqueue a job (e.g. `GenerateAnalystReportJob`), do not block HTTP requests